<paragraph id="8BDB4209E83BFFCEFF1F1BA1FBFF2F44" blockId="1.[174,1233,388,1854]" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">
Diagnosis. The new species is characterized by the following combination of characters: body brownish dorsally, creamy white ventrally; propodeum aciculate; metapleuron smooth, with few isolated setae; ovipositor weakly upcurved, the length from tip of hypopygium about 1.6× the length of hind tibia; hind wing with nervellus reclivous, distance between first abscissa of 
<emphasis id="B9109E1BE83BFFCEFDC91820FDBE2F45" box="[565,591,517,542]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">M</emphasis>
+ 
<emphasis id="B9109E1BE83BFFCEFDA31820FD702F44" box="[607,641,517,543]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">Cu</emphasis>
about 1.3× longer than vein 
<emphasis id="B9109E1BE83BFFCEFC281820FBF62F45" box="[980,1031,517,542]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">cu-a</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDB4209E83BFFCEFF1F1801FCC82E04" blockId="1.[174,1233,388,1854]" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">
<taxonomicName id="4C64398AE83BFFCEFF1F1801FE252F65" authority="Varga, 2021" authorityName="Varga" authorityYear="2021" box="[227,468,548,574]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Clistopyga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="422" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kenyensis" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="B9109E1BE83BFFCEFF1F1801FE252F65" box="[227,468,548,574]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">Clistopyga kenyensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B9109E1BE83BFFCEFE1D1800FDD62F64" bold="true" box="[481,551,549,575]" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2232360E83BFFCEFE1D1800FDD62F64" box="[481,551,549,575]" pageId="1" pageNumber="422" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
differs from both recorded Afrotropical species by the colouration: mesopleuron almost entirely creamy white (from black to red in 
<taxonomicName id="4C64398AE83BFFCEFBB71860FB212F05" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1793" box="[1099,1232,581,607]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Clistopyga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="422" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="incitator">
<emphasis id="B9109E1BE83BFFCEFBB71860FB212F05" box="[1099,1232,581,607]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">C. incitator</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and orange with a central yellow stripe in 
<taxonomicName id="4C64398AE83BFFCEFD3B1840FCBF2F24" authorityName="Benoit" authorityYear="1956" box="[711,846,613,639]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Clistopyga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="422" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="africana">
<emphasis id="B9109E1BE83BFFCEFD3B1840FCBF2F24" box="[711,846,613,639]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">C. africana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); metasomal tergites brownish, creamy white subapically (in both 
<taxonomicName id="4C64398AE83BFFCEFDB018A0FD222FC5" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1793" box="[588,723,645,671]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Clistopyga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="422" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="incitator">
<emphasis id="B9109E1BE83BFFCEFDB018A0FD222FC5" box="[588,723,645,671]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">C. incitator</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C64398AE83BFFCEFCED18A0FC652FC4" authorityName="Benoit" authorityYear="1956" box="[785,916,645,671]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Clistopyga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="422" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="africana">
<emphasis id="B9109E1BE83BFFCEFCED18A0FC652FC4" box="[785,916,645,671]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">C. africana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
metasoma is more-or-less unicolour). In addition, it differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C64398AE83BFFCEFD701880FCE42FE5" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1793" box="[652,789,677,703]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Clistopyga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="422" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="incitator">
<emphasis id="B9109E1BE83BFFCEFD701880FCE42FE5" box="[652,789,677,703]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">C. incitator</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the smooth and almost glabrous metapleuron (densely pubescent distally in 
<taxonomicName id="4C64398AE83BFFCEFD4E18E0FCC92F85" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1793" box="[690,824,709,735]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Clistopyga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="422" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="incitator">
<emphasis id="B9109E1BE83BFFCEFD4E18E0FCC92F85" box="[690,824,709,735]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">C. incitator</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and the aciculate first metasomal tergite (punctate in 
<taxonomicName id="4C64398AE83BFFCEFE6018C0FDD32FA5" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1793" box="[412,546,741,767]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Clistopyga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="422" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="incitator">
<emphasis id="B9109E1BE83BFFCEFE6018C0FDD32FA5" box="[412,546,741,767]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">C. incitator</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). The newly described species differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C64398AE83BFFCEFBD418C0FB5A2FA4" authorityName="Benoit" authorityYear="1956" box="[1064,1195,741,767]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Clistopyga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="422" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="africana">
<emphasis id="B9109E1BE83BFFCEFBD418C0FB5A2FA4" box="[1064,1195,741,767]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">C. africana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the thinner and longer ovipositor (about 1.6× the length of hind tibia in 
<taxonomicName id="4C64398AE83BFFCEFC071920FB792E45" authority="Varga, 2021" authorityName="Varga" authorityYear="2021" box="[1019,1160,772,799]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Clistopyga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="422" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kenyensis" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="B9109E1BE83BFFCEFC071920FB792E45" box="[1019,1160,772,799]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">C. kenyensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B9109E1BE83BFFCEFB731920FB212E44" bold="true" box="[1167,1232,773,799]" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2232360E83BFFCEFB731920FB212E44" box="[1167,1232,773,799]" pageId="1" pageNumber="422" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
comparing to 1.3 × in 
<taxonomicName id="4C64398AE83BFFCEFE4A1900FDC92E64" authorityName="Benoit" authorityYear="1956" box="[438,568,805,831]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Clistopyga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="422" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="africana">
<emphasis id="B9109E1BE83BFFCEFE4A1900FDC92E64" box="[438,568,805,831]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">C. africana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and the longer legs (hind femur 4.7× longer than wide in 
<taxonomicName id="4C64398AE83BFFCEFF301960FEAB2E05" authority="Varga, 2021" authorityName="Varga" authorityYear="2021" box="[204,346,836,863]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Clistopyga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="422" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kenyensis" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="B9109E1BE83BFFCEFF301960FEAB2E05" box="[204,346,836,863]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">C. kenyensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B9109E1BE83BFFCEFE9D1960FE532E04" bold="true" box="[353,418,837,863]" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2232360E83BFFCEFE9D1960FE532E04" box="[353,418,837,863]" pageId="1" pageNumber="422" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
comparing to 4.0× in 
<taxonomicName id="4C64398AE83BFFCEFD5B1960FCD92E04" authorityName="Benoit" authorityYear="1956" box="[679,808,837,863]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Clistopyga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="422" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="africana">
<emphasis id="B9109E1BE83BFFCEFD5B1960FCD92E04" box="[679,808,837,863]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">C. africana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDB4209E83BFFCEFF1F1941FE752EC4" blockId="1.[174,1233,388,1854]" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">
Description. 
<typeStatus id="54DFFCABE83BFFCEFE661941FDFA2E25" box="[410,523,868,894]" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">Holotype</typeStatus>
. Female (
<figureCitation id="135F5E8CE83BFFCEFD871941FD462E24" box="[635,695,868,895]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[166,199,1186,1208]" captionTargetBox="[247,1151,174,1162]" captionTargetId="figure-251@2.[247,1152,174,1162]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 1. Clistopyga kenyensis sp. n.: A, C–G — holotype female; B — paratype male; A–B — lateral view of habitus; С — frontal view of head; D — lateral view of metapleuron; E — dorsal view of metasomal tergites 1–3; F — dorsal view of head and mesosoma; G — lateral view of the ovipositor tip. Scale bar 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6456080" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6456080/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">fig. 1</figureCitation>
, A, C–G). Body length approximately 
<quantity id="4C9CEFECE83BFFCEFB7F1940FB3A2E24" box="[1155,1227,869,895]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="422" unit="mm" value="8.0">8 mm</quantity>
, fore wing 
<quantity id="4C9CEFECE83BFFCEFED819A1FE712EC4" box="[292,384,900,927]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" pageId="1" pageNumber="422" unit="mm" value="5.5">5.5 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDB4209E83BFFCEFF1F1980FD2429E5" blockId="1.[174,1233,388,1854]" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">
<emphasis id="B9109E1BE83BFFCEFF1F1980FED42EE4" bold="true" box="[227,293,933,959]" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">Head</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="135F5E8CE83BFFCEFED31981FE962EE4" box="[303,359,932,959]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[166,199,1186,1208]" captionTargetBox="[247,1151,174,1162]" captionTargetId="figure-251@2.[247,1152,174,1162]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 1. Clistopyga kenyensis sp. n.: A, C–G — holotype female; B — paratype male; A–B — lateral view of habitus; С — frontal view of head; D — lateral view of metapleuron; E — dorsal view of metasomal tergites 1–3; F — dorsal view of head and mesosoma; G — lateral view of the ovipositor tip. Scale bar 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6456080" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6456080/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">fig.1</figureCitation>
,C)generally smooth and sparsely pubescent.Antenna with25flagellomeres, first flagellomere 1.5× as long as second flagellomere. Maximum diameter of lateral ocellus 0.9 × as long as ocellar-ocular distance. Inner margins of eyes weakly emarginated opposite antennal sockets. Face about 0.7× as long as wide, smooth, sparsely pubescent. Clypeus strongly convex, about 0.4× as long as wide, distinctly separated from face and with the same sculpture, its apical margin concave and weakly notched. Malar space about as long as the basal width of mandible, subocular sulcus distinct. Upper tooth of mandible weakly longer than lower tooth. Occipital carina distinct, concave downwards dorsally. Temple strongly narrowed behind eye, gently rounded.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDB4209E83BFFCEFF1F1EE0FCAD2B64" blockId="1.[174,1233,388,1854]" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">
<emphasis id="B9109E1BE83BFFCEFF1F1EE0FE972984" bold="true" box="[227,358,1221,1247]" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">Mesosoma</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="135F5E8CE83BFFCEFE891EE1FE402984" box="[373,433,1220,1247]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[166,199,1186,1208]" captionTargetBox="[247,1151,174,1162]" captionTargetId="figure-251@2.[247,1152,174,1162]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 1. Clistopyga kenyensis sp. n.: A, C–G — holotype female; B — paratype male; A–B — lateral view of habitus; С — frontal view of head; D — lateral view of metapleuron; E — dorsal view of metasomal tergites 1–3; F — dorsal view of head and mesosoma; G — lateral view of the ovipositor tip. Scale bar 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6456080" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6456080/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">fig. 1</figureCitation>
, D, F). Propleuron smooth, sparsely pubescent. Pronotum smooth, epomia present, but short. Mesoscutum smooth and densely pubescent, with notauli strong, reaching the middle of mesoscutum, central lobe aciculate. Scutellum convex, smooth, sparsely pubescent, with lateral carina present basally. Mesopleuron smooth, sparsely pubescent, epicnemial carina present on lower 0.7 of mesopleuron. Metapleuron smooth, with few insolated setae, submetapleural carina distinct, pleural carina distinct before spiracles, weakly defined after spirales, almost indistinct (
<figureCitation id="135F5E8CE83BFFCEFCA91FA1FC6028C4" box="[853,913,1412,1439]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[166,199,1186,1208]" captionTargetBox="[247,1151,174,1162]" captionTargetId="figure-251@2.[247,1152,174,1162]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 1. Clistopyga kenyensis sp. n.: A, C–G — holotype female; B — paratype male; A–B — lateral view of habitus; С — frontal view of head; D — lateral view of metapleuron; E — dorsal view of metasomal tergites 1–3; F — dorsal view of head and mesosoma; G — lateral view of the ovipositor tip. Scale bar 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6456080" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6456080/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">fig. 1</figureCitation>
, D). Propodeum aciculate, with only lateromedian longitudinal carinae present on apical 0.1. Legs slender, hind femur 4.7× longer than wide, fifth tarsomere about as long as third tarsomere. Fore wing with areolet opened (vein 3 
<emphasis id="B9109E1BE83BFFCEFE481FC0FE1B28A5" box="[436,490,1509,1534]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">rs-m</emphasis>
absent); vein 2 
<emphasis id="B9109E1BE83BFFCEFD671FC0FD2028A5" box="[667,721,1509,1534]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">rs-m</emphasis>
short, about 0.3× the distance between 2 
<emphasis id="B9109E1BE83BFFCEFB4E1FC0FF342B45" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">rsm</emphasis>
and 2 
<emphasis id="B9109E1BE83BFFCEFEED1C20FEBC2B45" box="[273,333,1541,1566]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">m-cu</emphasis>
; vein 
<emphasis id="B9109E1BE83BFFCEFE6B1C20FE3B2B45" box="[407,458,1541,1566]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">cu-a</emphasis>
opposite to 
<emphasis id="B9109E1BE83BFFCEFD9D1C20FD5C2B44" box="[609,685,1541,1567]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">Rs&amp;M</emphasis>
. Hind wing with nervellus reclivous, distance between first abscissa of 
<emphasis id="B9109E1BE83BFFCEFE311C00FE162B65" box="[461,487,1573,1598]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">M</emphasis>
+ 
<emphasis id="B9109E1BE83BFFCEFE041C00FDEB2B64" box="[504,538,1573,1599]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">Cu</emphasis>
1.3× longer than vein 
<emphasis id="B9109E1BE83BFFCEFCDE1C00FCA42B65" box="[802,853,1573,1598]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">cu-a</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDB4209E83BFFCEFF1F1C60FBEC2A65" blockId="1.[174,1233,388,1854]" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">
<emphasis id="B9109E1BE83BFFCEFF1F1C60FE922B04" bold="true" box="[227,355,1605,1631]" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">Metasoma</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="135F5E8CE83BFFCEFE8E1C61FE5B2B04" box="[370,426,1604,1631]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[166,199,1186,1208]" captionTargetBox="[247,1151,174,1162]" captionTargetId="figure-251@2.[247,1152,174,1162]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 1. Clistopyga kenyensis sp. n.: A, C–G — holotype female; B — paratype male; A–B — lateral view of habitus; С — frontal view of head; D — lateral view of metapleuron; E — dorsal view of metasomal tergites 1–3; F — dorsal view of head and mesosoma; G — lateral view of the ovipositor tip. Scale bar 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6456080" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6456080/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">fig. 1</figureCitation>
, E, G) generally strongly sculptured and densely pubescent. First tergite about 1.3× as long as apical width, aciculate, with lateromedian oblique grooves weak, almost indistinct; dorsolateral carina distinct on basal 0.2 of the tergite; median longitudinal carina distinct and strong, reaching the apex of the tergite; glymma present. Second tergite about as long as apical width, rugulo-punctate, with basal and apical oblique grooves forming a rhombic convex area. Tergites 3–5 densely punctate, but punctures with scattered margins, with two lateromediam swellings; the remaining tergites weaker sculptured.Ovipositor(
<figureCitation id="135F5E8CE83BFFCEFBF91D21FBCB2A44" box="[1029,1082,1796,1823]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[166,199,1186,1208]" captionTargetBox="[247,1151,174,1162]" captionTargetId="figure-251@2.[247,1152,174,1162]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 1. Clistopyga kenyensis sp. n.: A, C–G — holotype female; B — paratype male; A–B — lateral view of habitus; С — frontal view of head; D — lateral view of metapleuron; E — dorsal view of metasomal tergites 1–3; F — dorsal view of head and mesosoma; G — lateral view of the ovipositor tip. Scale bar 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6456080" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6456080/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">fig.1</figureCitation>
,G) upcurved and thin, the length from tip of hypopygium about 1.6× the length of hind tibia.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF1B1281E838FFCDFF5A1E87FBB629B5" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6456080" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6456080" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6456080/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="423" startId="2.[166,199,1186,1208]" targetBox="[247,1151,174,1162]" targetPageId="2">
<paragraph id="8BDB4209E838FFCDFF5A1E87FBB629B5" blockId="2.[166,1224,1186,1262]" pageId="2" pageNumber="423">
Fig. 1. 
<taxonomicName id="4C64398AE838FFCDFF101E86FE4129E3" authority="Varga, 2021" authorityName="Varga" authorityYear="2021" box="[236,432,1187,1208]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Clistopyga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="423" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kenyensis" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="B9109E1BE838FFCDFF101E86FE4129E3" box="[236,432,1187,1208]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="423">Clistopyga kenyensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B9109E1BE838FFCDFE451E86FE0029E3" bold="true" box="[441,497,1187,1208]" pageId="2" pageNumber="423">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2232360E838FFCDFE451E86FE0029E3" box="[441,497,1187,1208]" pageId="2" pageNumber="423" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
: A, C–G — holotype female; B — paratype male; A–B — lateral view of habitus; С — frontal view of head; D — lateral view of metapleuron; E — dorsal view of metasomal tergites 1–3; F — dorsal view of head and mesosoma; G — lateral view of the ovipositor tip. Scale bar 0.1 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BDB4209E838FFCDFF271F22FDA428BA" blockId="2.[166,1225,1286,1729]" pageId="2" pageNumber="423">C o l o u r a t i o n. Body generally brownish dorsally, creamy white ventrally.Head creamy white except apex of mandible, frons centrally, occiput brownish and flagellum orange. Mesosoma creamy white except mesoscutum partly and propodeum dorsally brownish. Legs creamy white except stripes on hind coxa and hind femur, hind tibia subbasally and apically and tarsus entirely brownish. Metasoma orange with central areas brownish; all tergites creamy white subapically, tergites 1–3 with lateroapical stripes black. Pterostigma and veins brown. Ovipositor orange.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDB4209E838FFCDFF271FC3FBC12B1B" blockId="2.[166,1225,1286,1729]" pageId="2" pageNumber="423">
Male (
<figureCitation id="135F5E8CE838FFCDFED81FC3FEAC2B5A" box="[292,349,1510,1537]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[166,199,1186,1208]" captionTargetBox="[247,1151,174,1162]" captionTargetId="figure-251@2.[247,1152,174,1162]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 1. Clistopyga kenyensis sp. n.: A, C–G — holotype female; B — paratype male; A–B — lateral view of habitus; С — frontal view of head; D — lateral view of metapleuron; E — dorsal view of metasomal tergites 1–3; F — dorsal view of head and mesosoma; G — lateral view of the ovipositor tip. Scale bar 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6456080" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6456080/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="423">fig. 1</figureCitation>
, B) generally resembles female, but has smaller body (length approximately 7.0 mm, fore wing 5.0 mm), and some differences in colouration: metasoma with first tergite entirely and tergites 2–4 apicolaterally black; hind tibia with indistinct bands.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDB4209E838FFCDFF271C62FE582BDA" blockId="2.[166,1225,1286,1729]" pageId="2" pageNumber="423">
V a r i a b i l i t y. 
<typeStatus id="54DFFCABE838FFCDFE781C62FE1A2B3A" box="[388,491,1607,1633]" pageId="2" pageNumber="423">Paratype</typeStatus>
female has largely yellow head contrasting with creamy white meso- and metasoma.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDB4209E838FFCDFF271CA2FCCB2BFA" blockId="2.[166,1225,1286,1729]" box="[219,826,1670,1697]" pageId="2" pageNumber="423">
D i s t r i b u t i o n. Currently known only from 
<collectingCountry id="F3730299E838FFCDFD141CA2FCC72BFA" box="[744,822,1671,1697]" name="Kenya" pageId="2" pageNumber="423">Kenya</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDB4209E838FFCDFF271C83FBAF2B9B" blockId="2.[166,1225,1286,1729]" box="[219,1118,1702,1729]" pageId="2" pageNumber="423">Etymology. This species is named after the country, where it was collected.</paragraph>
